google tips to read quicker. You'll feel less mental exertion, and instead of feeling sleepy after a reading session, you'll feel a rush.

don't subvocalize. (don't say the word in your mind, just lift the information with your eyes and "know" it)
chunking. rather than scanning word by word, instead look at 3 to 5 words at once, then skip forward and read the next 3 to 5 words together.
don't re-read. don't day dream.
don't try to read fast. Just pick a comfortable pace and keep that pace.
